The Kaduna State Ministry of Business Innovation and Technology has exposed exporters in the state to the new import system of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, which commenced on 1st January 2021. At a one-day stakeholders forum organised by the ministry in collaboration with the Export Promotion Council exporters were enlightened on the benefits of the new system and counseled on how to take advantage of the system to expand their business. Speaking at the forum, the commissioner in the ministry said he called the meeting to deliberate on the new system and discuss the way forward that will ensure we maximise from whatever opportunities that are made available. “Nigerians will access UK GSP preferences under the general framework that reduces tariffs on certain product lines to low-income and lower middle-income countries.”